    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential null pointer dereference in format_get_next_token function\n\n### Summary\nThe `format_get_next_token` function in the tracer database parser could potentially cause a segmentation fault when processing malformed format strings with consecutive separators. While testing different trace configurations, we observed occasional crashes during database initialization.\n\nThis fix restructures the token parsing logic to eliminate the goto statement and improve code clarity while maintaining the exact same functionality.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/database.c`: Refactored format_get_next_token() to use explicit if-else control flow instead of goto\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/database.c`: Maintained all existing functionality and parsing behavior\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure tracing with a malformed FORMAT string containing consecutive separators\n2. Initialize the tracer database\n3. Observe potential segfault during token parsing\n\nThe symptoms include:\n- Segmentation fault during tracer initialization\n- Inconsistent behavior when parsing format strings with unusual spacing\n- Memory allocation errors in debug builds\n\n"
}